# ── LumiFilm Blockchain Configuration ──────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your deployed contract addresses.
# Leave empty to run in demo mode (mock data, no real transactions).

# Deployed contract addresses (from Ganache + Remix/Hardhat)
VITE_LUMI_TOKEN_ADDRESS=0x...
VITE_CROWDFUNDING_ADDRESS=0x...
VITE_GOVERNANCE_VOTING_ADDRESS=0x...
VITE_MILESTONE_ESCROW_ADDRESS=0x...

# Ganache network settings (defaults match Ganache Desktop)
VITE_GANACHE_CHAIN_ID=1337
VITE_GANACHE_RPC_URL=HTTP://127.0.0.1:7545

# ── How to deploy ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. Open Ganache Desktop and start a workspace.
#    Note the RPC URL and Chain ID shown in the settings.
#
# 2. In MetaMask: Add Network → use the RPC URL and Chain ID from Ganache.
#    Import a Ganache account by copying its private key into MetaMask.
#
# 3. Open Remix IDE (https://remix.ethereum.org):
#    a. Create LumiToken.sol → compile → deploy (no constructor args).
#    b. Copy the deployed LumiToken address.
#    c. Create LumiCrowdfunding.sol → compile → deploy (pass LumiToken address).
#    d. Copy the deployed LumiCrowdfunding address.
#    e. Back in LumiToken: call setMinter(LumiCrowdfunding address).
#       This allows the crowdfunding contract to mint LUMI rewards.
#
#    f. Deploy LumiGovernanceVoting.sol (pass LumiCrowdfunding address).
#    g. Deploy LumiMilestoneEscrow.sol (pass LumiCrowdfunding address).
#
# 4. Paste all deployed addresses into this .env file, then restart the dev server.
